The basic recipe for a decoction includes 1-pt water and 1-oz of herb or root. Place the water into a pot made from non-reactive metal (such as stainless or enamel; do not use aluminum). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut or crush the herb or root and add it to the water in the pot. (Do not cut or crush the herb or root in advance, as vital constituents can be lost. ){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Turn on the heat to medium. Simmer your decoction with the lid off until the volume of water is reduced by one-quarter (so, three-quarters of a pint remains). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a3/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a3/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cool and strain. Store in the fridge for no more than 72 hours. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Take in divided doses according to use. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Decoction-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
